{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eb718c4b-0278-4f44-aeb6-d561512a73ac","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncCleanup\n{\n    // TestContext is injected via constructor (MSTest 3.3+)\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous init here (e.g., create objects, set fields)\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization (runs before each test)\n    public Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // await async setup work here\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup (runs after each test)\n    public Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        return Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(TestContext);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — use for sync init and `TestContext` injection (no more `[TestInitialize]` needed for simple cases)\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`** — implement for async setup (replaces `[TestInitialize] async Task`)\n- **`IAsyncCleanup`** — the async teardown counterpart\n- The constructor runs first, then `InitializeAsync`, then the test, then `CleanupAsync`\n\nThis replaces the older `[TestInitialize]` / `[TestCleanup]` attribute pattern and the `TestContext` property-setter injection.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cd5a6f16-9b13-4791-ac94-6d9e7c729842","outputTokens":392,"requestId":"5C28:11D3F8:1F93F94:240C5DB:69F55349"},"id":"29057e7c-5270-4abe-9d9e-6c38a6b45095","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:28:50.506Z","parentId":"3e6d6f3f-0367-4dce-b5b9-c2ea357983ba"}
